SIMPLE: entre
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entre
<hw>En`tr⟦eacute⟧e"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Entry</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A coming in, or entrance; hence,
freedom of access; permission or right to enter; <as>as, to have the
<ex>entr⟦eacute⟧e</ex> of a house</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>In French usage, a dish served
at the beginning of dinner to give zest to the appetite; in English
usage, a side dish, served with a joint, or between the courses, as a
cutlet, scalloped oysters, etc.</def> <mark>[obsolescent]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>the dish which comprises the main course of a meal,
especially in a restaurant; <as>as, there were many <ex>entrees</ex> on
the menu</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entremets</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
